{{Short description|Mountain in Scotland}} {{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}} {{Infobox mountain | name = A' Ghlas-bhienn | photo = The summit of A' Ghlas-bheinn - geograph.org.uk - 519738.jpg | photo_caption = The summit of A' Ghlas-bhienn | elevation_m = 918 | elevation_ref =<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hill-bagging.co.uk/mountaindetails.php?rf=846 |title= A' Ghlas-bheinn |publisher=hill-bagging.co.uk|accessdate=10 May 2019}}</ref> | prominence_m = 407 | prominence_ref = | listing = [[List of Munro mountains in Scotland|Munro]], [[Marilyn (hill)|Marilyn]] | translation = | language = | pronunciation = | location = [[Ross and Cromarty]], [[Scotland]] | range = [[Northwest Highlands]] | map = Scotland Highland | grid_ref_UK = NH008230 | topo = [[Ordnance Survey|OS]] ''Landranger'' 25 33 | easiest_route = }}
'''A' Ghlas-bhienn''' (918 m) is a mountain in the [[Northwest Highlands]] of Scotland. It lies in the [[Kintail]] area of [[Ross-shire]], close to the settlement of [[Morvich]].
A rocky peak, its ascent can be done in conjunction with the [[Falls of Glomach]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.walkhighlands.co.uk/munros/a-ghlas-bheinn |title= walkhighlands A' Ghlas-bhienn|publisher=walkhighlands.co.uk|accessdate=10 May 2019}}</ref>
